				<td colspan="2"><span>The 5% makes this song a joke...yer right.  I want to see this song do 15% then it will be usefull enough to sing.
<br />

<br />
15% might actually get you to the cap before it wears off.  The max damage it can reduce is 450...and the max it will take off the hit is 5%,,,so depending ob the mob hitting you, it could take a long time to get the 5% hits to actually hit the 450 cap.
<br />

<br />
Moving the cap does NOT change the 5% rule.  It just means that the incoming mele hits are reduced by 5% until the 1500 is reached then it wears off....like that is going to happen.
<br />

<br />
What we need is a realistic value of reduction so that right when the rune wears off you have actually used up all 1500 hps....15% might be the number we need here.
<br />

<br />

<br />
15% would make an 800 hitter hit you for 680...120 less and after 8 hits you would have used up all 1500 hps.  On a slowed mob, this is about right.  Maybe it needs to be 15% and 2000hps come to think about it.<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
Edit...we need to test, but the belief over at Backstage is that the 450 hps does NOT scale up with the wind mod...oh, oh...really a useless song now. 5% and 450hps non scaling...the plus stats probably does scale.  yipee 25 to all.
<br />

<br />
