				<td colspan="2"><span>Got the song, memmed it, pulsed it once, put it to the back of the songbook.  The numbers are fine for a song with zero recast.  The percent and the total absorbtion need to be affected by instrument if the recast is kept.  If one or the other doesn't happen, it stays in the category of wasted rune.
<br />

<br />
Consider that this song will mitigate less damage than a level 60 ranger heal, and you see why it isn't worth the hassle to try to twist in.  The recast means you have to either have a stupidly complex twist, or you drop songs.  The benefit of this song isn't worth dropping any other song I am playing.
