				<td colspan="2"><span>I think the percentage of mitigation also changes with instrument mods.  While on an uqua raid i noticed i was taking roughly 880 damage from a AE spell blast.  When i started twisting in VoV i was taking 771.  Now i have a 2.8 mod with winds, so that should be a 14% mitigation instead of 5%.  The numbers i listed only support a 12.5% mitigation so perhaps there is a hard cap.  While this song is a pain to twist, it DOES make a difference.  If used in a 5 song twist, especially with amp, you can keep it up more of the time.
<br />
For tanks i tend to use Warmarch of mastruq, amp, veeshan, nivs, and VoV. Alternate amp and VoV and you shouldnt have a problem.</span></td>
